== Hindi ==

=== Pronunciation ===
/ k<sup>h</sup>ə / as the c in English <b>c</b>at. [[Aspirated]]
[[voiceless]] [[velar]] [[plosive]].

===Definition===

Consonant of the [[Devanagari]] script.

===Variant form===
*With a [[nukta]](small diacritic dot) ([[ख़]]) the character is used to represent / xə / the voiceless velar fricative, a sound borrowed from Persian. It is similar to the ending of the German doch.  Many Hindi dialects will pronounce words with the borrowed sound as / k<sup>h</sup>ə /.

